Ring Foundation - A.narrow concrete perimeter around the outside of a dwelling.
Piles - Vertical structural elements being the base of the foundation.

Joists’- Runs on or between bearers to create a frame for the floor.

Bearers - Thick horizontal elements running over piles to create load support.

