SUMMARY

Please read this report in its entirety. This summary is for information purposes and is not a substitute for the
information provided in the body of this report. This summary will include aspects we consider most relevant.
The house is in a combination of generally good and average condition through different elements» Areas of
remediation and maintenance are commented on in this report.

Roof

There is general denting noted to the decromastic tiles, the coating has degraded throughout, there are
popped nail fixings, and there is some general spot rust to the southern roof element. Remediation is
possible, however, a full roof replacement is likely a more cost effective option. There is currently no
substantial weather tightness risk with the roof cladding, however, the cladding is aged and. general
remediation on it would be a reasonable and expensive task to carry out properly. It is recommended the cost
of a full re-roof be taken into consideration when purchasing this home. The gutter to.the north eastern
element has rusted right through to the soffit and needs replacement. The gutters should be cleared out of
debris and comprehensively checked over by a suitably qualified specialist. All rusted sections should be
replaced. Flashings around the chimney should be sealed and adjusted.to prevent water pooling on them.
Concrete capping in the top of the chimney should be replaced as it has cracking through it.

Exterior

Water damaged soffit sheets should be replaced once the gutter leaks have been fixed. The weatherboards
on the garage gable end need replacing. The rest of the weatherboards.are generally fine but are in need of
a repaint or stain to prevent them aging. Some minor re-pointing needed to any cracking to the mortar on the
brick cladding. Check rubber seals on joinery and replace any that have perished or shrunk.

Structure

Several wet and elevated moisture readings taken. Please refer to. moisture section of this report for
comments.

Interior

Some painting and decorating needed to improve the interior. Some rotting noted to two of the garage door
reveals. These sections are best replaced. The interior doors.are in general need of attention and adjusting
to improve them.

Plumbing

Monitor hot water cylinder as it is very dated and may be near the end of its life expectancy. It is
recommended that an extraction fan be installed to the bathroom. Refer to moisture section of this report
regarding shower stall leak.

